Great prof! Does not assign readings. Very easy - one group project based on a company, a quiz, and a take-home final. He explains things very well and it is obvious that he teaches for the joy of it.

This professor was one of the worst. He cancelled two full classes of 3 hours each throughout the session and offered no makeup classes, meaning we rushed through all of the material. There was a midterm paper worth 30%, a presentation worth 20% and final paper worth 50% and all of his directions were very unclear. Don't take this prof!

Prof. Samer is a practicing marketer so he teaches with a "real world" focus.  I found his high tech marketing course interesting and useful however those in class who had no real industry experience had a hard time relating to the material.
